data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,hetərou'dʒinjəs]
*tính từ
 ■hỗn tạp, khác thể, không đồng nhất

Anh - Anh
heterogeneous
[ˌhɛt(ə)rə(ʊ)'dʒi:nɪəs, -'dʒɛn-]
■ adjective
1》 diverse in character or content.
2》 Chemistry denoting a process involving substances in different phases (solid, liquid, or gaseous): heterogeneous catalysis.
Derivatives
heterogeneity-dʒɪ'ni:ɪti, -'neɪɪti noun
heterogeneouslyadverb
heterogeneousnessnoun
Origin
C17: from med. L. heterogeneus, from Gk heterogenēs, from heteros 'other' + genos 'a kind'.
Usage
Heterogeneous is commonly misspelled as heterogenous. Heterogenous is actually a different word, meaning ‘originating outside the organism’.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
heterogeneous
▸ adjective DIVERSE, varied, varying, miscellaneous, assorted, mixed, sundry, disparate, different, differing, unrelated; motley; poetic/literary divers.
Opposites
homogeneous.
